# Release Lifecycle

## Rolling Pre-releases (RC workflow)

Each version stream gets **one pre-release** that is updated in place as RCs progress. Never create a new release for each RC — edit the existing one.

### Version streams
- Android: `android-v{X.Y.Z}-rc`
- Firmware USB: `fw-usb-v{X.Y}-rc`
- Firmware Pro: `fw-pro-v{X.Y}-rc`

### Creating the first RC (e.g. rc.1)

1. Set `rcSuffix=rc.1` in `android/gradle.properties` (for Android streams)
2. Commit, tag, and push:
   ```bash
   git tag -a android-v2.2.4-rc.1 -m "v2.2.4-rc.1"
   git push origin android-v2.2.4-rc.1
   gh release create android-v2.2.4-rc.1 --prerelease --target staging \
     --title "android-v2.2.4-rc.1" --notes "<notes>" <artifacts>
   ```

### Updating to a new RC (e.g. rc.1 → rc.8)

Instead of creating a new release, **update the existing one**:

1. **Update `rcSuffix`** in `android/gradle.properties` to the new RC number (e.g. `rcSuffix=rc.8`)

2. **Move the tag** to the new commit:
   ```bash
   git tag -d android-v2.2.4-rc.1
   git push origin :refs/tags/android-v2.2.4-rc.1
   git tag -a android-v2.2.4-rc.8 -m "v2.2.4-rc.8: <summary>"
   git push origin android-v2.2.4-rc.8
   ```

2. **Edit the release** — update tag, title, and notes:
   ```bash
   gh release edit android-v2.2.4-rc.1 --tag android-v2.2.4-rc.8 \
     --title "android-v2.2.4-rc.8" --notes "<updated notes>"
   ```
   If `gh release edit` doesn't support `--tag`, delete and recreate:
   ```bash
   gh release delete android-v2.2.4-rc.1 --yes
   gh release create android-v2.2.4-rc.8 --prerelease --target staging \
     --title "android-v2.2.4-rc.8" --notes "<notes>" <artifacts>
   ```

3. **Replace artifacts** (APK / firmware binaries):
   ```bash
   gh release delete-asset android-v2.2.4-rc.8 openRS_v2.2.4.apk --yes
   gh release upload android-v2.2.4-rc.8 android/app/build/outputs/apk/release/openRS_v2.2.4.apk
   ```

4. **Ensure the release is not in draft** (tag moves can flip it to draft):
   ```bash
   gh release edit android-v2.2.4-rc.8 --draft=false --prerelease
   ```

### Result
- Only **one pre-release per version stream** exists at any time
- The release notes contain the full cumulative changelog (current RC + "Previous RCs" section)
- No cleanup needed — the releases page stays clean

## Promoting to Stable

When the RC is ready for production:

1. **Clear `rcSuffix`** — set `rcSuffix=` (empty) in `android/gradle.properties`
2. Merge `staging` → `main`
3. Create a new **stable release** tag (e.g. `android-v2.2.4`)
4. Delete the RC pre-release
5. Create the stable release with `--latest`

## Scope

- Firmware USB (`fw-usb-*`) and Pro (`fw-pro-*`) are separate streams
- Android (`android-*`) is its own stream
- Each stream has at most **one** pre-release at a time
